PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F416A1781888761
OL,3,CApology and damages for Eugene Reavey
OL,4,Cwhose brothers were murdered 50 years
OL,5,Cago
OL,7,FAnnouncing the agreed terms, Mr Fahy
OL,8,Fsaid: "The Chief Constable
OL,9,Facknowledges the generational grief
OL,10,Fand trauma that have been suffered by
OL,11,Fthe plaintiff and his family as a
OL,12,Fresult of these murders.
OL,14,F"The Chief Constable apologies to the
OL,15,Fplaintiff for the inadequacies in the
OL,16,Finvestigation of these murders and
OL,17,Facknowledges that these failures have
OL,18,Fcaused additional distress to the
OL,19,Fplaintiff and his family."
OL,26,@vD@AOU{D@ZO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G7/9
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
